data.chText: 特定年份（或地方）酿制的酒；酿造年份
data.enText: the wine that was produced in a particular year or place; the year in which it was produced

data.chText: 采摘葡萄酿酒的期间（或季节）；葡萄收获期（或季节）
data.enText: the period or season of gathering grapes for making wine

data.chText: 这次葡萄的收获季节比往常晚。
data.enText: The vintage was later than usual.

data.chText: （指葡萄酒）优质的，上等的，佳酿的
data.enText: vintage wine is of very good quality and has been stored for several years

data.chText: 古色古香的（指1917–1930年间制造，车型和品味受人青睐的）
data.enText: made between 1917 and 1930 and admired for its style and interest

data.chText: （过去某个时期）典型的，优质的；（某人的）最佳作品的
data.enText: typical of a period in the past and of high quality; the best work of the particular person

data.chText: 这部歌剧是罗西尼的最佳代表作。
成绩卓著的一年；成功的一年
data.enText: a particularly good and successful year

data.chText: 2003年对电影业来说不是全盛之年。
data.enText: 2003 was not a vintage year for the movies.

word_means: 古色古香的(指1917–1930年间制造，车型和品味受人青睐的)

means: 特定年份(或地方)酿制的酒
采摘葡萄酿酒的期间(或季节)
(指葡萄酒)优质的，上等的，佳酿的
古色古香的(指1917–1930年间制造，车型和品味受人青睐的)
(过去某个时期)典型的，优质的

tr: a season's yield of wine from a vineyard

value.def: The vintage of a good quality wine is the year and place that it was made before being stored to improve it. You can also use vintage to refer to the wine that was made in a certain year.

example.ex: Many predict 1991 will rival the great vintage of 1965...
example.tran: 许多人预测1991年酿制的葡萄酒可以与1965年生产的佳酿相媲美。

example.ex: This wine is from one of the two best vintages of the decade in this region...
example.tran: 这种酒是该地区这10年来两个葡萄丰收旺年之一所产的佳酿。

example.ex: The 1985 vintage has a stronger bouquet and slight caramelly flavour.
example.tran: 这种1985年酿制的陈年佳酿味道更醇厚，带有一种淡淡的焦糖甜味。

value.tran: （某优质葡萄酒的）产地和年份;特定年份酿的葡萄酒

value.def: Vintage wine is good quality wine that has been stored for several years in order to improve its quality.

example.ex: If you can buy only one case at auction, it should be vintage port.
example.tran: 如果你在拍卖会上只能买一样东西，那就应该是上等的波尔图葡萄酒。

value.tran: （葡萄酒）优质的，上等的，佳酿的

value.def: Vintage cars or aeroplanes are old but are admired because they are considered to be the best of their kind.

example.ex: The museum will have a permanent exhibition of 60 vintage cars.
example.tran: 这个博物馆将长期展出60辆老爷车。

value.tran: （汽车或飞机)老式的，古色古香的

value.def: You can use vintage to describe something which is the best and most typical of its kind.

example.ex: At the press conference, James is on vintage form...
example.tran: 在这次记者招待会上，詹姆斯的表现最出色。

example.ex: This is vintage comedy at its best.
example.tran: 这是这类喜剧中的代表性作品。

trans: 佳酿葡萄酒；精制葡萄酒
